WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.792 --> 00:00:03.211
VISERYS TARGARYEN:
I. Viserys Targaryen.

2
00:00:03.753 --> 00:00:05.714
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.

3
00:00:05.964 --> 00:00:10.635
do hereby name Rhaenyra
Targaryen heir...

4
00:00:12.137 --> 00:00:13.596
<i>to the Iron Throne.</i>

5
00:00:14.973 --> 00:00:18.143
♪ (FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYS)

6
00:00:19.602 --> 00:00:23.564
The King will die. and
if Rhaenyra succeeds him.

7
00:00:23.565 --> 00:00:25.150
<i>war will follow.</i>

8
00:00:25.275 --> 00:00:26.775
<i>The realm will not accept her.</i>

9
00:00:26.776 --> 00:00:28.278
<i>And to secure her claim.</i>

10
00:00:28.403 --> 00:00:30.947
<i>she'll have to put your
children to the sword.</i>

11
00:00:31.656 --> 00:00:33.240
ALICENT HIGHTOWER:
<i>Criston Cole will be named</i>

12
00:00:33.241 --> 00:00:35.326
<i>Lord Commander of
the Kingsguard.</i>

13
00:00:36.077 --> 00:00:38.163
<i>I trust you and your loyalty.</i>

14
00:00:38.288 --> 00:00:39.664
I will not fail you.

15
00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:41.332
I need you. Uncle.

16
00:00:41.791 --> 00:00:45.128
(SPEAKING IN HIGH VALYRIAN)

17
00:00:47.589 --> 00:00:48.589
VISERYS: Rhaenyra...

18
00:00:48.590 --> 00:00:49.631
(THUNDER)

19
00:00:49.632 --> 00:00:50.759
You wanted to know.

20
00:00:51.134 --> 00:00:52.802
Aegon's dream.

21
00:00:53.470 --> 00:00:54.595
The Song of Ice...

22
00:00:54.596 --> 00:00:55.637
(THUNDER)

23
00:00:55.638 --> 00:00:56.681
and Fire.

24
00:00:57.182 --> 00:00:59.017
The Prince That Was Promised.

25
00:00:59.351 --> 00:01:01.186
<i>- Aegon.</i>
- ALICENT: <i>Our son.</i>

26
00:01:01.311 --> 00:01:02.645
I understand. my King.

27
00:01:06.524 --> 00:01:07.650
The King is dead.

28
00:01:08.485 --> 00:01:10.319
ARRYK CARGYLL: <i>Aegon
is unfit to rule.</i>

29
00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:12.488
You tolerated the Prince's
proclivities for years.

30
00:01:12.489 --> 00:01:14.199
Because it was my
sworn duty. Arryk.

31
00:01:14.366 --> 00:01:17.534
When you install your
grandson on the throne.

32
00:01:17.535 --> 00:01:20.705
<i>remember it was me
who put him there.</i>

33
00:01:21.206 --> 00:01:22.665
OTTO HIGHTOWER:
<i>I will remember.</i>

34
00:01:24.209 --> 00:01:26.335
SPEAKER: <i>All hail His Grace!</i>

35
00:01:26.336 --> 00:01:27.961
You are usurping the throne.

36
00:01:27.962 --> 00:01:30.005
SPEAKER: <i>Lord of the
Seven Kingdoms...</i>

37
00:01:30.006 --> 00:01:31.341
She will never bend the knee.

38
00:01:31.508 --> 00:01:33.801
SPEAKER: <i>and Protector
of the Realm.</i>

39
00:01:33.802 --> 00:01:37.681
- (COMMOTION)
- (MELEYS ROARS)

40
00:01:39.015 --> 00:01:41.810
(MELEYS SCREECHES)

41
00:01:42.352 --> 00:01:45.397
A war is like to be fought over
this treachery. to be sure.

42
00:01:46.064 --> 00:01:47.732
I swear to ward the Queen.

43
00:01:47.857 --> 00:01:51.069
OTTO: <i>Alicent has not forgotten
the love you had for each other.</i>

44
00:01:51.194 --> 00:01:53.028
<i>No blood need be spilled.</i>

45
00:01:53.029 --> 00:01:55.699
<i>so the realm can
carry on in peace.</i>

46
00:01:56.032 --> 00:01:58.575
That girl destroys
everything she touches.

47
00:01:58.576 --> 00:02:00.536
RHAENYS TARGARYEN: <i>Every man
standing 'round the Painted Table</i>

48
00:02:00.537 --> 00:02:02.080
<i>urges her to plunge
the realm into war.</i>

49
00:02:02.205 --> 00:02:03.664
DAEMON TARGARYEN: <i>The
enemy have declared war.</i>

50
00:02:03.665 --> 00:02:05.375
What are you gonna do about it?

51
00:02:06.334 --> 00:02:09.253
You have the full support
of our fleet and house.

52
00:02:09.254 --> 00:02:11.171
RHAENYRA TARGARYEN: <i>Prince
Jacaerys will fly north</i>

53
00:02:11.172 --> 00:02:12.257
<i>to Winterfell.</i>

54
00:02:12.674 --> 00:02:15.427
<i>Prince Lucerys will fly
south to Storm's End.</i>

55
00:02:15.927 --> 00:02:19.764
<i>We must remind these lords
of the oaths they swore.</i>

56
00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:22.684
I want you to put out your eye.

57
00:02:22.892 --> 00:02:23.892
No.

58
00:02:24.019 --> 00:02:27.229
Give me your eye or I
will take it. bastard!

59
00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:29.274
♪ (MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

60
00:02:31.568 --> 00:02:33.445
- (VHAGAR GROWLS)
- (ARRAX YELPS)

61
00:02:34.237 --> 00:02:35.447
AEMOND TARGARYEN: <i>No!</i>

62
00:02:38.616 --> 00:02:40.536
RHAENYS: <i>The Greens are
coming for you. Rhaenyra.</i>

63
00:02:41.244 --> 00:02:42.620
♪ (MUSIC FADES OUT)

64
00:02:50.253 --> 00:02:53.423
(epic theme playing)

65
00:03:42.514 --> 00:03:46.976
♪

66
00:04:29.352 --> 00:04:31.521
(theme concludes)

67
00:04:38.695 --> 00:04:40.612
(birds chirping)

68
00:04:40.613 --> 00:04:43.365
(ambient nature sounds)

69
00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:46.661
(light music playing)

70
00:04:48.246 --> 00:04:50.248
(raven caws)

71
00:04:57.505 --> 00:04:59.424
♪

72
00:04:59.549 --> 00:05:01.718
(wind blowing)

73
00:05:07.849 --> 00:05:11.061
speaker: <i>Duty is sacrifice.</i>

74
00:05:12.103 --> 00:05:14.397
<i>It eclipses all things.</i>

75
00:05:14.522 --> 00:05:16.232
<i>even blood.</i>

76
00:05:17.734 --> 00:05:21.071
<i>All men of honor
must pay its price.</i>

77
00:05:25.408 --> 00:05:29.078
<i>The North owes a great
duty to the Seven Kingdoms.</i>

78
00:05:29.079 --> 00:05:31.872
<i>- One older than any oath.</i>
- (dog barking)

79
00:05:31.873 --> 00:05:33.792
<i>Since the days of the First Men.</i>

80
00:05:33.917 --> 00:05:36.377
<i>we have stood as guardians</i>

81
00:05:36.378 --> 00:05:38.254
<i>against the cold and the dark.</i>

82
00:05:39.714 --> 00:05:41.424
<i>Through its long tradition.</i>

83
00:05:41.549 --> 00:05:43.634
<i>the Night's Watch
cultivated its strength</i>

84
00:05:43.635 --> 00:05:45.095
<i>from doomed men</i>

85
00:05:45.220 --> 00:05:47.846
<i>who had their life as
their only possession.</i>

86
00:05:47.847 --> 00:05:50.683
<i>But my ancestor. Torrhen Stark.</i>

87
00:05:50.684 --> 00:05:52.768
<i>began a tradition by
making an offering</i>

88
00:05:52.769 --> 00:05:55.105
<i>at the onset of winter:</i>

89
00:05:55.230 --> 00:05:57.564
<i>one in 10 men from our household</i>

90
00:05:57.565 --> 00:06:00.902
<i>was to be chosen to
fortify the Watch.</i>

91
00:06:03.488 --> 00:06:08.742
<i>This is not a
sentence but an honor.</i>

92
00:06:08.743 --> 00:06:12.831
<i>A duty embraced by all
who serve the North.</i>

93
00:06:12.956 --> 00:06:15.249
<i>Even by mine own kin.</i>

94
00:06:15.250 --> 00:06:17.460
♪

95
00:06:17.585 --> 00:06:20.338
(wind blowing)

96
00:06:20.463 --> 00:06:22.966
<i>The North must stand ready.</i>

97
00:06:24.300 --> 00:06:25.718
<i>Winter is coming.</i>

98
00:06:25.719 --> 00:06:27.928
Coming? What is this. then.

99
00:06:27.929 --> 00:06:29.930
that falls from the skies
and shivers my bones?

100
00:06:29.931 --> 00:06:33.726
This is only a late
summer snow. my prince.

101
00:06:33.727 --> 00:06:36.145
In winter. it will
cover all you see.

102
00:06:36.146 --> 00:06:39.732
and all memories of
warmth will be forgotten.

103
00:06:39.733 --> 00:06:41.942
It pleases me to think
that over a century ago

104
00:06:41.943 --> 00:06:44.946
our ancestors treated
in this very place.

105
00:06:45.989 --> 00:06:48.158
The Conqueror and the
King in the North.

106
00:06:49.826 --> 00:06:51.536
You. at least. had the mercy

107
00:06:51.661 --> 00:06:53.830
not to threaten me
with your dragon.

108
00:06:53.955 --> 00:06:56.332
(lift creaks loudly)

109
00:07:00.211 --> 00:07:02.172
(distant shouting)

110
00:07:02.297 --> 00:07:03.922
My prince.

111
00:07:03.923 --> 00:07:06.176
- My lord.
- My lord.

112
00:07:07.052 --> 00:07:08.260
M'lord.

113
00:07:08.261 --> 00:07:10.555
Surely the great Torrhen Stark

114
00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:13.515
would've sooner died
than bent the knee.

115
00:07:13.516 --> 00:07:14.785
Unless he believed the Conqueror

116
00:07:14.809 --> 00:07:17.187
could bring unity to
the Seven Kingdoms.

117
00:07:18.480 --> 00:07:20.022
You are right in that.

118
00:07:20.023 --> 00:07:22.484
That unity is now threatened.

119
00:07:23.193 --> 00:07:25.861
The realm will soon
tear itself apart...

120
00:07:25.862 --> 00:07:26.863
if men do not remember

121
00:07:26.988 --> 00:07:28.698
the oath sworn to King Viserys

122
00:07:29.032 --> 00:07:31.158
and to his rightful heir.

123
00:07:31.159 --> 00:07:34.829
Starks do not forget
their oaths. my prince.

124
00:07:35.205 --> 00:07:37.664
But you must know
that my gaze is

125
00:07:37.665 --> 00:07:40.210
forever torn between
north and south.

126
00:07:41.211 --> 00:07:44.589
In winter. my duty to the
Wall is even more dire

127
00:07:44.714 --> 00:07:46.424
than the one I owe
to King's Landing.

128
00:07:46.549 --> 00:07:48.634
I need my men here.

129
00:07:48.635 --> 00:07:49.843
Whilst your men guard against

130
00:07:49.844 --> 00:07:51.637
wildlings and weather.

131
00:07:51.638 --> 00:07:54.432
the Hightowers plan
to usurp the throne.

132
00:07:55.100 --> 00:07:57.435
If my mother is to
defend her claim

133
00:07:57.560 --> 00:07:58.686
to hold the realm united.

134
00:07:58.687 --> 00:08:00.187
she needs an army.

135
00:08:00.188 --> 00:08:01.022
War is coming

136
00:08:01.023 --> 00:08:03.066
to the whole of
the realm. my lord.

137
00:08:03.191 --> 00:08:06.236
We cannot wage it without
the support of the North.

138
00:08:07.237 --> 00:08:09.239
(wind blowing)

139
00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:16.036
My father brought King Jaehaerys

140
00:08:16.037 --> 00:08:18.456
and Queen Alysanne
to see the Wall.

141
00:08:19.082 --> 00:08:21.750
His Grace stood at
this very outlook

142
00:08:21.751 --> 00:08:23.795
and watched as their dragons.

143
00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:26.423
the greatest power in the world.

144
00:08:26.548 --> 00:08:28.550
refused to cross it.

145
00:08:30.051 --> 00:08:31.844
Do you think my ancestors built

146
00:08:31.845 --> 00:08:33.887
a 700-foot wall of ice

147
00:08:33.888 --> 00:08:36.933
to keep out snow and savages?

148
00:08:37.058 --> 00:08:39.102
What does it keep out?

149
00:08:41.104 --> 00:08:42.438
Death.

150
00:08:42.439 --> 00:08:45.900
(light. tense music playing)

151
00:08:50.238 --> 00:08:52.531
I have thousands of graybeards

152
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:54.908
who've already seen
too many winters.

153
00:08:54.909 --> 00:08:58.412
They are... well-honed.

154
00:08:58.413 --> 00:09:00.790
So they're old?

155
00:09:00.915 --> 00:09:03.709
I can ready them
to march at once.

156
00:09:03.710 --> 00:09:05.003
If your graybeards can fight.

157
00:09:05.128 --> 00:09:07.463
the queen will have them.

158
00:09:07.464 --> 00:09:09.381
They will fight hard.

159
00:09:09.382 --> 00:09:10.967
Like Northerners.

160
00:09:11.092 --> 00:09:12.134
Stark captain: My lord?

161
00:09:12.135 --> 00:09:15.472
- (footsteps approaching)
- A raven's arrived.

162
00:09:15.597 --> 00:09:17.474
Urgent news from Dragonstone.

163
00:09:30.362 --> 00:09:33.365
(tense music playing)

164
00:09:37.202 --> 00:09:38.953
(roars)

165
00:09:45.293 --> 00:09:47.003
(Meleys roars)

166
00:09:51.132 --> 00:09:53.134
(Rhaenys speaks High Valyrian)

167
00:09:53.385 --> 00:09:55.637
(dragonkeeper speaks
High Valyrian)

168
00:09:59.891 --> 00:10:03.395
Take your mount again.
We're flying out.

169
00:10:05.980 --> 00:10:09.567
I alone patrol over a
hundred miles of open sea.

170
00:10:09.693 --> 00:10:12.529
endlessly. to hold the blockade.

171
00:10:13.238 --> 00:10:17.033
Meleys must gorge
and rest. as must I.

172
00:10:18.243 --> 00:10:20.828
- We're going to King's Landing.
- To what end?

173
00:10:20.829 --> 00:10:22.287
Killing Vhagar.

174
00:10:22.288 --> 00:10:25.332
I cannot face that
hoary old bitch alone.

175
00:10:25.333 --> 00:10:26.959
With my dragon and
yours together.

176
00:10:26.960 --> 00:10:29.670
we can kill Vhagar
and her rider.

177
00:10:29.671 --> 00:10:31.214
Make it a son for a son.

178
00:10:33.216 --> 00:10:35.927
- Was this the queen's command?
- The queen remains absent.

179
00:10:36.052 --> 00:10:37.970
I should be at
Harrenhal bending knees.

180
00:10:37.971 --> 00:10:40.724
but I must instead remain
here to wage her war.

181
00:10:40.849 --> 00:10:43.268
Or perhaps. more simply.
to await her return.

182
00:10:43.393 --> 00:10:46.771
She has been gone for days.
Too long. She is exposed.

183
00:10:46.896 --> 00:10:49.023
- She is grieving.
- The mother grieves

184
00:10:49.024 --> 00:10:51.568
as the queen shirks her duties.

185
00:10:53.361 --> 00:10:57.698
It was a raven that brought
me news of Laena's death.

186
00:10:57.699 --> 00:11:00.909
I existed for
weeks in torment...

187
00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:04.080
refusing to believe
what I'd been told.

188
00:11:05.749 --> 00:11:08.667
It was only when I saw my
daughter's mortal remains

189
00:11:08.668 --> 00:11:11.254
that I could begin to mourn her.

190
00:11:13.381 --> 00:11:17.260
A raven has told Rhaenyra
that her son is dead.

191
00:11:18.219 --> 00:11:19.762
She needs to know
it for certain.

192
00:11:19.763 --> 00:11:21.806
She was a fool to go alone.

193
00:11:22.432 --> 00:11:24.100
What if Aemond were
to happen upon her?

194
00:11:24.225 --> 00:11:26.269
Then I would pity Aemond.

195
00:11:28.772 --> 00:11:30.899
The queen was wise
to recuse herself.

196
00:11:31.775 --> 00:11:37.237
She has not acted on the vengeful
impulse that others might have.

197
00:11:37.238 --> 00:11:40.407
If you'd have acted when
you had the chance...

198
00:11:40.408 --> 00:11:43.411
Aegon's line would
be extinguished.

199
00:11:44.621 --> 00:11:47.082
And Luke would be alive.

200
00:11:53.963 --> 00:11:55.674
Fly with me.

201
00:11:56.299 --> 00:12:00.136
- It is a command.
- Would that you were the king.

202
00:12:03.640 --> 00:12:06.600
(solemn music playing)

203
00:12:06.601 --> 00:12:08.645
(dragons calling)

204
00:12:19.531 --> 00:12:22.534
♪

205
00:12:30.333 --> 00:12:33.670
(workers chattering. shouting)

206
00:12:37.173 --> 00:12:39.384
(animals chattering)

207
00:12:51.354 --> 00:12:53.690
(people greeting Corlys)

208
00:13:09.873 --> 00:13:11.207
M'lord.

209
00:13:13.585 --> 00:13:17.213
It's a marvel she was able to
return from the Stepstones at all.

210
00:13:19.341 --> 00:13:21.176
Barely done. but done.

211
00:13:21.551 --> 00:13:25.263
Seven more ships put out to sea
this morn' to fortify the blockade.

212
00:13:25.388 --> 00:13:27.806
The Gullet is vast. and we're
not like to have the numbers

213
00:13:27.807 --> 00:13:30.226
to cover all that open water.

214
00:13:32.604 --> 00:13:34.646
Corlys Velaryon: I must
have my ship back at sea

215
00:13:34.647 --> 00:13:35.732
to lead the effort.

216
00:13:35.857 --> 00:13:38.735
Alyn of Hull: It'll be
many weeks yet. I'd wager.

217
00:13:40.403 --> 00:13:41.946
But I'll have a word
with my brother...

218
00:13:42.781 --> 00:13:46.409
to see what reinforcements
the shipwrights can muster.

219
00:13:56.086 --> 00:13:58.880
The smithy delivered
this earlier.

220
00:14:00.965 --> 00:14:02.384
M'lord?

221
00:14:10.725 --> 00:14:14.104
I had this commissioned
for Prince Lucerys.

222
00:14:15.897 --> 00:14:19.109
I was very sorry to hear
about your heir's death.

223
00:14:19.567 --> 00:14:21.778
'Twas the blackest
of treacheries.

224
00:14:24.781 --> 00:14:29.618
Pardon. m'lord. if it'll
please you. much to do.

225
00:14:29.619 --> 00:14:30.995
They tell me that
you are the one

226
00:14:31.121 --> 00:14:33.331
that dragged my
body out of the sea.

227
00:14:38.461 --> 00:14:40.338
It was only my duty.

228
00:14:44.634 --> 00:14:47.929
I am indebted to you. Alyn.

229
00:14:59.983 --> 00:15:03.152
(light. tense music playing)

230
00:15:03.153 --> 00:15:05.947
(ambient nature sounds)

231
00:15:14.039 --> 00:15:16.291
♪

232
00:15:20.837 --> 00:15:23.673
- (indistinct chatter)
- (horse neighs)

233
00:15:25.175 --> 00:15:27.177
(soldier shouting)

234
00:15:27.344 --> 00:15:29.304
Mind your posts!

235
00:15:32.015 --> 00:15:34.184
Keep your focus. men!

236
00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:40.023
- Guard 1 (shouts): Dragon!
- Guard 2 (shouts): Dragon!

237
00:15:40.148 --> 00:15:41.524
Arm the scorpion!

238
00:15:41.649 --> 00:15:44.194
Guard 1 (shouts):
Arm the scorpion!

239
00:15:45.653 --> 00:15:48.155
Approaching from the southeast!

240
00:15:48.156 --> 00:15:49.366
Get around!

241
00:15:49.491 --> 00:15:51.534
- (scorpion creaking)
- (guard shouting)

242
00:15:54.037 --> 00:15:55.454
guard (shouts):
Scorpion ready!

243
00:15:55.455 --> 00:15:58.374
- Arryk Cargyll (shouts): Halt!
- Guard (shouts): Halt!

244
00:15:58.375 --> 00:16:00.710
(Vhagar grumbles)

245
00:16:00.835 --> 00:16:02.127
Stand down. it's Vhagar!

246
00:16:02.128 --> 00:16:04.046
Guard 2: Stand down!

247
00:16:04.047 --> 00:16:06.007
Guard 1: Standing down!

248
00:16:10.220 --> 00:16:12.430
(scorpion creaking)

249
00:16:14.265 --> 00:16:16.226
(Vhagar grumbles)

250
00:16:16.351 --> 00:16:18.561
(quiet chatter)

251
00:16:32.909 --> 00:16:34.744
Where is Jaehaerys?

252
00:16:36.079 --> 00:16:38.248
Attending his lessons.

253
00:16:38.915 --> 00:16:40.417
And those are where?

254
00:16:40.542 --> 00:16:42.042
What do you need of him?

255
00:16:42.043 --> 00:16:44.169
Taking him to the small council.

256
00:16:44.170 --> 00:16:45.212
He'll be king one day.

257
00:16:45.213 --> 00:16:47.215
He must begin his instruction.

258
00:16:47.549 --> 00:16:49.926
What if he does not
want to be king?

259
00:16:51.052 --> 00:16:52.261
(whispers) Where is he?

260
00:16:52.262 --> 00:16:53.430
The library.

261
00:16:53.722 --> 00:16:56.433
You must not
interrupt his custom.

262
00:17:03.106 --> 00:17:04.774
I'm afraid.

263
00:17:07.152 --> 00:17:08.319
Don't be.

264
00:17:08.945 --> 00:17:11.864
They'd be fools to come with
Vhagar protecting the city.

265
00:17:11.865 --> 00:17:13.950
Not the dragons.

266
00:17:14.826 --> 00:17:15.994
The rats.

267
00:17:24.794 --> 00:17:27.589
The queen is an
enduring mystery...

268
00:17:28.131 --> 00:17:29.674
is she not?

269
00:17:34.346 --> 00:17:36.598
(birds chirping)

270
00:17:38.975 --> 00:17:40.977
(heavy breathing)

271
00:17:42.145 --> 00:17:44.356
(quiet moaning)

272
00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:55.992
(birds cawing)

273
00:18:03.375 --> 00:18:05.377
There's a chill in the air.

274
00:18:09.464 --> 00:18:11.841
Summer is well
and truly through.

275
00:18:13.009 --> 00:18:16.054
We are expected at the
small council. Your Grace.

276
00:18:31.861 --> 00:18:33.363
We cannot.

277
00:18:33.905 --> 00:18:35.073
Again.

278
00:18:38.076 --> 00:18:39.828
Yes. Your Grace.

279
00:18:44.374 --> 00:18:46.543
If you wouldn't mind?

280
00:18:50.714 --> 00:18:53.883
(light music playing)

281
00:19:04.394 --> 00:19:06.563
(dog whimpers)

282
00:19:07.772 --> 00:19:09.774
♪

283
00:19:19.242 --> 00:19:21.910
- Tyland Lannister: Your Grace.
- Alicent Hightower: Good day.

284
00:19:21.911 --> 00:19:23.955
♪

285
00:19:26.082 --> 00:19:28.561
Aegon Targaryen: Hello! Jaehaerys
must learn the ways of the court

286
00:19:28.585 --> 00:19:30.502
if he is to rule
one day. (laughs)

287
00:19:30.503 --> 00:19:32.922
Up we go. (laughs)

288
00:19:33.757 --> 00:19:36.216
Good morrow. my lords.

289
00:19:36.217 --> 00:19:37.469
Mother.

290
00:19:39.429 --> 00:19:41.055
What news?

291
00:19:41.056 --> 00:19:43.682
Otto Hightower: Our letters
to the Vale and to the North

292
00:19:43.683 --> 00:19:46.102
continue to go unanswered.

293
00:19:46.770 --> 00:19:47.771
Cunts.

294
00:19:49.272 --> 00:19:51.565
Otto: The Stormlands
should be ours

295
00:19:51.566 --> 00:19:53.318
after Prince Aemond's
marriage pact

296
00:19:53.443 --> 00:19:55.527
to the Lady Floris Baratheon.

297
00:19:55.528 --> 00:19:57.696
I anticipate their
sworn declaration.

298
00:19:57.697 --> 00:20:01.784
(sighs) My brother is raising
the strength of the West

299
00:20:01.785 --> 00:20:05.079
to mass at the Golden
Tooth. but we...

300
00:20:05.080 --> 00:20:06.622
Yeah. thank you. my prince.

301
00:20:06.623 --> 00:20:09.125
That's. that's very helpful.

302
00:20:09.250 --> 00:20:10.584
My nephew. Lord Ormund.

303
00:20:10.585 --> 00:20:13.796
musters his forces to
sally forth from Oldtown.

304
00:20:13.797 --> 00:20:15.214
They expect to march quickly.

305
00:20:15.215 --> 00:20:18.802
meeting little resistance.
until they reach the Riverlands.

306
00:20:18.927 --> 00:20:20.803
My letters to Rhaenyra.
Has there been any answer?

307
00:20:20.804 --> 00:20:23.555
An apology for her dead son?

308
00:20:23.556 --> 00:20:24.974
None. Your Grace.

309
00:20:25.100 --> 00:20:27.185
Between that and their
blockade of the Gullet.

310
00:20:27.310 --> 00:20:29.436
we must presume that
the princess has refused

311
00:20:29.437 --> 00:20:30.855
the offered terms.

312
00:20:30.980 --> 00:20:33.358
and that war is now inevitable.

313
00:20:33.483 --> 00:20:35.628
- Jaehaerys Targaryen: Na-na!
- Perhaps Your Grace might lend

314
00:20:35.652 --> 00:20:37.987
- his voice to our outreach...
- Tyland: Stop! Enough!

315
00:20:38.655 --> 00:20:40.906
In hopes that new terms
might. might be negotiated.

316
00:20:40.907 --> 00:20:43.826
Release it at once!
Would someone please?

317
00:20:43.827 --> 00:20:46.996
Is the heir to the throne
bothering you. Tyland?

318
00:20:48.206 --> 00:20:51.876
No. No. no. not. not in
the least. Your Grace.

319
00:20:52.002 --> 00:20:54.461
Because I think he wants a ride.

320
00:20:54.462 --> 00:20:55.940
- Alicent: Your Grace.
- Tyland: Uh. a ride?

321
00:20:55.964 --> 00:20:57.297
A pony ride.

322
00:20:57.298 --> 00:20:58.799
Wouldn't that be fun. Jaehaerys?

323
00:20:58.800 --> 00:21:01.344
Should the Master of
Coin be your royal steed?

324
00:21:01.469 --> 00:21:03.221
(light laughter)

325
00:21:10.520 --> 00:21:12.063
Your Grace!

326
00:21:12.856 --> 00:21:15.191
There are important
matters to discuss...

327
00:21:16.526 --> 00:21:18.570
despite Sir Tyland's
interruptions.

328
00:21:20.030 --> 00:21:21.364
Aegon: Very well.

329
00:21:21.990 --> 00:21:24.701
No time for amusements. Tyland.

330
00:21:26.036 --> 00:21:27.203
Your Grace.

331
00:21:28.038 --> 00:21:30.832
Aegon: Off you go.
Jaehaerys. Good boy.

332
00:21:33.209 --> 00:21:34.878
Where were we? (clears throat)

333
00:21:36.087 --> 00:21:40.425
Rhaenyra's blockade has placed
King's Landing under strain.

334
00:21:40.550 --> 00:21:42.719
And those pressures
will multiply quickly.

335
00:21:42.844 --> 00:21:44.864
Well. we should've just killed
her when we had the chance.

336
00:21:44.888 --> 00:21:48.349
Regrettably. the opportunity
for surprise has been lost.

337
00:21:48.350 --> 00:21:52.562
and with it. the chance to
end this conflict quickly.

338
00:21:53.688 --> 00:21:55.689
We must play the
board before us.

339
00:21:55.690 --> 00:21:58.233
Tyland: If we are to break
the Sea Snake's blockade.

340
00:21:58.234 --> 00:22:00.986
we will need to bolster both the
Lannister and Hightower navies.

341
00:22:00.987 --> 00:22:03.740
We do have need for a
new Master of Ships.

342
00:22:03.865 --> 00:22:07.034
We could offer the title to
the young Lord Dalton Greyjoy.

343
00:22:07.035 --> 00:22:09.411
Aemond. What is
your business here?

344
00:22:09.412 --> 00:22:10.580
The king summoned me.

345
00:22:10.705 --> 00:22:12.247
You do not have a
seat at this council.

346
00:22:12.248 --> 00:22:15.668
Aemond is my closest
blood and our best sword.

347
00:22:15.669 --> 00:22:17.253
I welcome him.

348
00:22:17.879 --> 00:22:20.799
Path to King's Landing is
through the Riverlands.

349
00:22:20.924 --> 00:22:24.343
We must establish a toehold
there. at Harrenhal.

350
00:22:24.344 --> 00:22:26.553
Aegon: The Riverlords will
either declare for me.

351
00:22:26.554 --> 00:22:29.390
or they will meet Vhagar
and Sunfyre together.

352
00:22:29.391 --> 00:22:31.850
Ah. and-and we can burn the
blockade while we're at it.

353
00:22:31.851 --> 00:22:33.704
- Rhaenyra has dragons as well.
- Mine are bigger.

354
00:22:33.728 --> 00:22:36.397
If we lose the dragons to war.
there'll be no calling them back.

355
00:22:36.398 --> 00:22:37.898
- We must proceed cautiously.
- No.

356
00:22:37.899 --> 00:22:42.194
Fat. old Lord Tully will either
raise my banner or see his burn.

357
00:22:42.195 --> 00:22:44.322
We should fly to Riverrun.

358
00:22:44.656 --> 00:22:46.324
You are the king. Your Grace.

359
00:22:46.449 --> 00:22:47.741
You must not put
yourself at risk.

360
00:22:47.742 --> 00:22:50.536
And Vhagar is needed here to
deter Rhaenyra from attacking

361
00:22:50.537 --> 00:22:53.289
in retribution for
the death of her son.

362
00:22:54.124 --> 00:22:58.585
Errors were made in the hours
following King Viserys's death.

363
00:22:58.586 --> 00:23:01.006
We mustn't compound them.

364
00:23:02.298 --> 00:23:04.967
You've already demonstrated
your might. Your Grace.

365
00:23:04.968 --> 00:23:09.430
- We must now favor patience and restraint.
- (Aegon sighs)

366
00:23:09.431 --> 00:23:11.056
I send ravens by the hour.

367
00:23:11.057 --> 00:23:15.561
Many and more houses will
declare for you in time.

368
00:23:15.562 --> 00:23:18.982
History and precedent
will come to your side.

369
00:23:19.607 --> 00:23:22.318
- (birds chirping)
- (indistinct chatter)

370
00:23:26.614 --> 00:23:27.699
Good morrow. Your Grace.

371
00:23:27.824 --> 00:23:29.450
Good morrow. Lord Larys.

372
00:23:29.451 --> 00:23:31.369
I had come earlier
to have a word

373
00:23:31.494 --> 00:23:33.038
before the small
council convened.

374
00:23:33.163 --> 00:23:37.959
but your handmaiden said
that you were indisposed.

375
00:23:40.962 --> 00:23:43.214
What is it you wish to discuss?

376
00:23:45.008 --> 00:23:49.595
I have completed questioning
the whole of the castle staff.

377
00:23:49.596 --> 00:23:51.305
They produced rather
interesting details.

378
00:23:51.306 --> 00:23:56.311
but I am satisfied I have exposed
all who betrayed our trust.

379
00:23:58.188 --> 00:23:59.356
And what of them?

380
00:24:00.690 --> 00:24:03.026
They no longer breathe our air.

381
00:24:05.028 --> 00:24:08.865
I have chosen your
new staff personally.

382
00:24:13.703 --> 00:24:15.413
(door opens)

383
00:24:16.706 --> 00:24:18.375
(door closes)

384
00:24:27.050 --> 00:24:29.427
St... Gi-Give me that.

385
00:24:29.552 --> 00:24:30.887
Maidservant: Your Grace?

386
00:24:31.429 --> 00:24:33.431
(sighs) Just leave me.

387
00:24:35.016 --> 00:24:37.227
Just le... Just
le... Just leave me.

388
00:24:40.897 --> 00:24:42.523
(door opens)

389
00:24:42.524 --> 00:24:45.401
(tense. pensive music playing)

390
00:24:45.402 --> 00:24:46.778
(door closes)

391
00:24:56.287 --> 00:24:57.580
♪

392
00:24:57.706 --> 00:24:59.416
(Syrax roars)

393
00:25:14.597 --> 00:25:16.808
♪

394
00:25:18.393 --> 00:25:19.811
(indistinct shouting)

395
00:25:19.936 --> 00:25:22.272
- It's a dragon wing!
- Let's have a look!

396
00:25:23.773 --> 00:25:25.942
- It's a wing.
- Who cares what it is.

397
00:25:26.651 --> 00:25:28.319
(yells) Dragon!

398
00:25:28.445 --> 00:25:30.447
(crowd yelling)

399
00:25:31.448 --> 00:25:33.158
(Syrax roars)

400
00:25:35.326 --> 00:25:37.495
(yelling. panicking)

401
00:25:41.624 --> 00:25:43.293
(roars)

402
00:25:49.632 --> 00:25:52.802
(solemn music playing)

403
00:26:16.785 --> 00:26:18.744
♪

404
00:26:18.745 --> 00:26:20.497
(crying)

405
00:26:37.972 --> 00:26:40.183
(Syrax grumbling)

406
00:26:44.562 --> 00:26:47.565
♪

407
00:26:53.321 --> 00:26:54.906
(Syrax roars)

408
00:26:55.031 --> 00:26:58.076
Leon Estermont: All
hail King Aegon!

409
00:26:58.201 --> 00:27:00.661
"Aegon the Magnanimous."

410
00:27:00.662 --> 00:27:03.206
Second of His Name.
King of the Andals.

411
00:27:03.331 --> 00:27:05.541
and the Rhoynar.
and the First Men.

412
00:27:05.542 --> 00:27:08.920
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

413
00:27:09.045 --> 00:27:11.714
Hail King Aegon!

414
00:27:11.715 --> 00:27:13.508
"The Magnanimous"?

415
00:27:17.220 --> 00:27:18.221
Your Grace.

416
00:27:18.680 --> 00:27:22.183
Let's have the first
petition. my good Lord Hand.

417
00:27:23.727 --> 00:27:24.936
(grunts)

418
00:27:26.271 --> 00:27:28.106
(nervously) Good morrow.
my. uh. Your Grace.

419
00:27:28.231 --> 00:27:29.607
- (laughter)
- Aegon: It's alright.

420
00:27:29.733 --> 00:27:31.692
There's no reason to be nervous.

421
00:27:31.693 --> 00:27:32.818
What's your name?

422
00:27:32.819 --> 00:27:35.029
Gr... Uh. Jerard. Your Grace.

423
00:27:35.030 --> 00:27:37.073
Good morrow. Jerard.

424
00:27:37.198 --> 00:27:39.784
And how might your
king be of service?

425
00:27:39.909 --> 00:27:42.327
'Tis my flock.

426
00:27:42.328 --> 00:27:46.291
Uh. a-a-a tenth of
them taken by...

427
00:27:48.084 --> 00:27:51.003
- the Crown on...
- (crowd murmuring)

428
00:27:51.004 --> 00:27:53.213
on the cusp of winter.

429
00:27:53.214 --> 00:27:56.426
- If I'd had the time to plan...
- We should return them.

430
00:27:59.304 --> 00:28:00.888
- Your Grace?
- Aegon: Well. you need

431
00:28:00.889 --> 00:28:02.389
your goats for the
winter. don't you?

432
00:28:02.390 --> 00:28:05.267
- Sheep. Your-Your Grace.
- Aegon: Sheep. even better.

433
00:28:05.268 --> 00:28:07.770
I shall make your
flock of sheep whole.

434
00:28:07.771 --> 00:28:09.396
(Jerard laughs)

435
00:28:09.397 --> 00:28:11.983
We already made a promise
to all the Crownlands

436
00:28:12.108 --> 00:28:14.319
that a tithing of livestock

437
00:28:14.444 --> 00:28:16.737
would be necessary to
sustain the dragons

438
00:28:16.738 --> 00:28:18.113
for their increased activity

439
00:28:18.114 --> 00:28:21.826
and. pray not.
eventual fighting.

440
00:28:21.951 --> 00:28:23.744
Right... Right.

441
00:28:23.745 --> 00:28:26.956
Perhaps we could just return
his sheep. He came all this way.

442
00:28:27.082 --> 00:28:29.501
If you return one herder's
sheep. Your Grace.

443
00:28:29.626 --> 00:28:32.086
you will soon find them all
at the foot of your throne

444
00:28:32.087 --> 00:28:34.546
expecting the same.

445
00:28:34.547 --> 00:28:35.965
They won't know.

446
00:28:36.091 --> 00:28:42.091
When the king speaks.
Your Grace. all hear it.

447
00:28:50.939 --> 00:28:53.858
After further thought.
I have decided that

448
00:28:53.983 --> 00:28:56.235
I cannot restore your sheep.

449
00:28:56.236 --> 00:28:57.653
If war were to break out.

450
00:28:57.654 --> 00:28:59.364
my dragons will require feed.

451
00:28:59.489 --> 00:29:02.241
- Bring the next.
- (crowd murmuring)

452
00:29:02.242 --> 00:29:05.994
guildmaster: Salts always run
scarce on the road to winter.

453
00:29:05.995 --> 00:29:06.996
Your Grace.

454
00:29:07.122 --> 00:29:08.914
We rely on ships from Essos

455
00:29:08.915 --> 00:29:10.333
for our supply.

456
00:29:10.458 --> 00:29:13.545
But now. with a blockade in
place and war threatening...

457
00:29:13.670 --> 00:29:15.796
Yeah. that treasonous
blockade won't last long.

458
00:29:15.797 --> 00:29:18.424
I plan to send Vhagar
to burn it to ash.

459
00:29:18.425 --> 00:29:19.675
Bring the next.

460
00:29:19.676 --> 00:29:21.803
(crowd murmuring)

461
00:29:23.722 --> 00:29:25.473
Hugh. Your Grace.

462
00:29:28.852 --> 00:29:30.185
The smiths are all proud

463
00:29:30.186 --> 00:29:32.647
to support Your Grace
against Rhaenyra.

464
00:29:36.401 --> 00:29:37.401
But?

465
00:29:37.485 --> 00:29:38.653
But...

466
00:29:40.196 --> 00:29:42.365
iron costs have grown.

467
00:29:43.158 --> 00:29:46.703
A lone scorpion
takes weeks to build.

468
00:29:47.328 --> 00:29:49.706
To put it simply.
we are struggling.

469
00:29:50.373 --> 00:29:54.877
If we could but have the Crown's
coin before we started work.

470
00:29:54.878 --> 00:29:56.670
it would bring great relief.

471
00:29:56.671 --> 00:30:00.383
Not just to me. but to all
the smiths serving your cause.

472
00:30:02.552 --> 00:30:03.720
(sighs)

473
00:30:04.888 --> 00:30:07.891
You shall be paid and paid well.

474
00:30:08.224 --> 00:30:10.392
My army cannot win a war
without your weapons.

475
00:30:10.393 --> 00:30:12.437
You should continue
their making.

476
00:30:12.729 --> 00:30:16.775
Our victory depends on the
efforts of the smallfolk.

477
00:30:19.110 --> 00:30:21.571
You have my most sincere
gratitude. Your Grace.

478
00:30:22.238 --> 00:30:24.908
Aegon: I'll hear
the next petition.

479
00:30:25.033 --> 00:30:27.243
(indistinct chatter)

480
00:30:31.748 --> 00:30:34.668
Larys Strong: Your Grace. it filled my
heart to see you on the Iron Throne.

481
00:30:34.709 --> 00:30:37.962
- (Aegon groans) - I was only a boy
when Jaehaerys last graced the seat.

482
00:30:38.088 --> 00:30:39.338
but you brought forth
memories of him.

483
00:30:39.339 --> 00:30:41.633
and you have such a deft
touch with the smallfolk.

484
00:30:41.758 --> 00:30:43.509
just as your father did.

485
00:30:43.510 --> 00:30:44.928
Thank you. my lord.

486
00:30:45.303 --> 00:30:47.722
I wonder. do you have a
moment for a quiet word?

487
00:30:53.603 --> 00:30:57.022
It is the Hand's wont to
keep a firm grip on things.

488
00:30:57.023 --> 00:30:59.191
Mm.

489
00:30:59.192 --> 00:31:01.444
He controlled your
father the same way.

490
00:31:02.779 --> 00:31:05.657
Viserys had a certain
reputation as being pliable.

491
00:31:05.782 --> 00:31:07.283
I am aware.

492
00:31:08.618 --> 00:31:11.036
I would think. as
we find ourselves

493
00:31:11.037 --> 00:31:13.247
standing within a
hair's breadth of war.

494
00:31:13.248 --> 00:31:16.459
that you would wish to
be viewed differently.

495
00:31:19.629 --> 00:31:20.879
How?

496
00:31:20.880 --> 00:31:22.674
Otto Hightower...

497
00:31:24.009 --> 00:31:27.137
was your father's
Hand. Your Grace.

498
00:31:43.653 --> 00:31:44.821
Daughter.

499
00:31:45.989 --> 00:31:48.700
I requested an
audience hours ago.

500
00:31:49.993 --> 00:31:53.830
There were many petitions.

501
00:31:56.332 --> 00:31:58.460
Alicent: I find
myself wondering...

502
00:31:59.336 --> 00:32:01.379
do we pursue the same end?

503
00:32:03.048 --> 00:32:06.843
I must admit. there are days
where I myself can't be sure.

504
00:32:08.386 --> 00:32:10.638
I shall tell you mine.

505
00:32:12.140 --> 00:32:13.474
It's victory.

506
00:32:13.475 --> 00:32:16.352
And how would you
define "victory"?

507
00:32:16.353 --> 00:32:18.312
Rhaenyra bending the knee

508
00:32:18.313 --> 00:32:21.232
and Aegon sitting the
Iron Throne. in peace.

509
00:32:21.858 --> 00:32:23.234
As Viserys wished.

510
00:32:23.360 --> 00:32:26.987
Well. if that's how you describe
it. then we are aligned.

511
00:32:26.988 --> 00:32:29.074
- Then be my ally.
- I am.

512
00:32:29.199 --> 00:32:30.759
An ally would not
repeatedly cut my legs

513
00:32:30.825 --> 00:32:32.744
from beneath me at
that table of men!

514
00:32:32.869 --> 00:32:36.497
- I sit there and I feel your anger.
- Frustration.

515
00:32:36.498 --> 00:32:38.874
These critical days
since Viserys's passing

516
00:32:38.875 --> 00:32:42.212
- haven't gone to plan.
- That's not my fault.

517
00:32:43.421 --> 00:32:46.383
My sons both see you
as the great example.

518
00:32:46.508 --> 00:32:47.842
The Hand to three kings.

519
00:32:49.386 --> 00:32:51.221
Aegon is ever-eager
to prove himself

520
00:32:51.346 --> 00:32:52.889
and Aemond...

521
00:32:54.349 --> 00:32:57.394
Aemond is angry.

522
00:32:57.519 --> 00:32:59.938
Rhaenyra's son took his eye
and was never punished for it.

523
00:33:00.063 --> 00:33:04.901
- What he did. however vicious...
- The caprice of youth.

524
00:33:08.947 --> 00:33:10.782
I could only hope.

525
00:33:10.907 --> 00:33:12.909
Aemond erred.

526
00:33:13.785 --> 00:33:17.329
But he is fiercely loyal.
He wishes to please.

527
00:33:17.330 --> 00:33:19.081
And Aegon still heeds me.

528
00:33:19.082 --> 00:33:20.792
In private. at least.

529
00:33:22.252 --> 00:33:23.544
But if you undermine my voice.

530
00:33:23.545 --> 00:33:25.421
both those boys will
grow deaf to it.

531
00:33:25.422 --> 00:33:28.717
(light music playing)

532
00:33:33.972 --> 00:33:35.932
I hadn't seen it that way.

533
00:33:36.391 --> 00:33:38.309
We only need to mind Aegon

534
00:33:38.435 --> 00:33:40.770
until the novelty
of rule is spent.

535
00:33:41.479 --> 00:33:44.565
Once he tires of it. you and I
can steer our cause to victory.

536
00:33:44.566 --> 00:33:47.318
A fine strategy. daughter.

537
00:33:47.902 --> 00:33:53.783
But you must accept that the path
to victory now is one of violence.

538
00:33:54.784 --> 00:33:56.453
I know it.

539
00:33:59.914 --> 00:34:02.459
But that does not mean
it must be wanton.

540
00:34:04.753 --> 00:34:05.754
No.

541
00:34:09.591 --> 00:34:12.802
(tense music playing)

542
00:34:19.142 --> 00:34:22.311
(indistinct shouting)

543
00:34:22.312 --> 00:34:24.814
solider (shouts):
Prepare to be boarded!

544
00:34:27.317 --> 00:34:30.362
By the order of Lord
Corlys Velaryon!

545
00:34:30.487 --> 00:34:33.113
Erryk Cargyll: Search
the hold for stowaways!

546
00:34:33.114 --> 00:34:35.367
♪

547
00:34:41.122 --> 00:34:43.124
(indistinct shouting)

548
00:34:51.508 --> 00:34:53.133
(goats bleating)

549
00:34:53.134 --> 00:34:55.387
(music fades out)

550
00:35:00.850 --> 00:35:01.851
You.

551
00:35:04.229 --> 00:35:07.649
When last we met.
there were two of you.

552
00:35:09.859 --> 00:35:10.984
"The White Worm."

553
00:35:10.985 --> 00:35:13.654
Mysaria: Did you think I
would wither in your absence?

554
00:35:13.655 --> 00:35:15.698
I did not think you
would flower a traitor.

555
00:35:15.699 --> 00:35:18.951
You speak of highborn
games. I am common-born.

556
00:35:18.952 --> 00:35:21.538
How long have you been selling
secrets to Otto Hightower?

557
00:35:21.663 --> 00:35:23.873
As long as he had
gold to pay for them.

558
00:35:25.917 --> 00:35:30.547
Who sent you fleeing from King's
Landing in such disrepair. hm?

559
00:35:31.715 --> 00:35:33.716
You put Aegon on the throne.

560
00:35:33.717 --> 00:35:35.801
That was the
Hightowers' conspiracy.

561
00:35:35.802 --> 00:35:38.430
I merely profited from
knowing Aegon's movements.

562
00:35:38.555 --> 00:35:39.889
But you delivered him.

563
00:35:40.015 --> 00:35:43.058
He would've returned home
eventually for gold and for respite.

564
00:35:43.059 --> 00:35:43.977
as he always does.

565
00:35:43.978 --> 00:35:47.063
I simply... simply sped
the business along.

566
00:35:47.188 --> 00:35:49.314
"Business" that ended with the
theft of the queen's throne

567
00:35:49.315 --> 00:35:50.524
and the murder of her son.

568
00:35:50.525 --> 00:35:52.484
You only blame me
because your true enemies

569
00:35:52.485 --> 00:35:54.446
are out of reach.

570
00:35:55.739 --> 00:35:57.197
My arrangement with the Hand

571
00:35:57.198 --> 00:35:58.657
was purely transactional.

572
00:35:58.658 --> 00:36:01.368
I held no loyalty to him.

573
00:36:01.369 --> 00:36:03.413
Certainly do not now.

574
00:36:03.872 --> 00:36:08.585
Otto Hightower was to me as I am to
your noble ilk. fodder to be cast off.

575
00:36:08.710 --> 00:36:10.336
What else do you know
of him? His plans?

576
00:36:10.337 --> 00:36:12.088
Little and less.

577
00:36:15.258 --> 00:36:18.636
I possess nothing of
value to you. Daemon.

578
00:36:29.272 --> 00:36:32.442
(gasps. breathes heavily)

579
00:36:36.613 --> 00:36:38.448
(door slams)

580
00:36:41.451 --> 00:36:42.827
Have her moved to the cells.

581
00:36:42.952 --> 00:36:45.789
She is to be treated as
a traitor to the crown.

582
00:36:48.458 --> 00:36:50.376
Erryk: Forgive
me. my prince...

583
00:36:50.377 --> 00:36:51.877
but the lady speaks the truth.

584
00:36:51.878 --> 00:36:55.298
- She was no agent of the Hightowers.
- What is it to you?

585
00:36:55.799 --> 00:36:58.550
- A matter of honor.
- Was it honor that made you stand by and watch

586
00:36:58.551 --> 00:37:01.304
as the Hightowers
usurped the throne?

587
00:37:01.429 --> 00:37:03.972
You and your traitorous twin.

588
00:37:03.973 --> 00:37:06.017
No. my prince.

589
00:37:07.310 --> 00:37:08.853
I'm shamed by it.

590
00:37:09.354 --> 00:37:11.481
That's why I abandoned
the Kingsguard.

591
00:37:11.606 --> 00:37:13.482
and my brother. and came here.

592
00:37:13.483 --> 00:37:16.068
I don't care.

593
00:37:16.069 --> 00:37:16.903
Aegon was in your grasp.

594
00:37:16.904 --> 00:37:18.822
You should've
killed him yourself.

595
00:37:18.947 --> 00:37:22.491
Arryk and I were named to the
Kingsguard at just 8 and 10.

596
00:37:22.492 --> 00:37:24.660
And we swore the same oath:

597
00:37:24.661 --> 00:37:27.122
to defend the whole
of the royal family.

598
00:37:28.164 --> 00:37:31.501
So what were we to do when they
turned against one another?

599
00:37:33.503 --> 00:37:35.672
(dragon roars)

600
00:37:40.510 --> 00:37:43.722
(tense music playing)

601
00:37:49.477 --> 00:37:51.688
♪

602
00:38:00.030 --> 00:38:04.283
Queen Rhaenyra Targaryen.
the First of Her Name.

603
00:38:04.284 --> 00:38:08.787
Queen of the Andals. and the
Rhoynar. and the First Men.

604
00:38:08.788 --> 00:38:13.042
Lady of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

605
00:38:13.043 --> 00:38:15.086
♪

606
00:38:18.882 --> 00:38:21.259
(whispers) Did you
find what you needed?

607
00:38:29.726 --> 00:38:32.687
Your council stands at
the ready. Your Grace.

608
00:38:36.566 --> 00:38:38.901
I will fly to Harrenhal
at your command

609
00:38:38.902 --> 00:38:41.196
and set our toehold
in the Riverlands.

610
00:38:41.946 --> 00:38:44.282
Your Grace. my lord husband's
blockade of the Gullet

611
00:38:44.407 --> 00:38:45.325
moves into place.

612
00:38:45.326 --> 00:38:46.533
All seaborne travel and trade

613
00:38:46.534 --> 00:38:48.912
to King's Landing
will soon be cut off.

614
00:38:49.037 --> 00:38:51.039
♪

615
00:38:54.793 --> 00:38:58.213
I want Aemond Targaryen.

616
00:38:59.214 --> 00:39:01.216
(music intensifies)

617
00:39:18.108 --> 00:39:20.110
♪

618
00:39:23.780 --> 00:39:25.949
(music fades out)

619
00:39:46.511 --> 00:39:49.096
In your years as a
merchant of gossip.

620
00:39:49.097 --> 00:39:51.765
you surely accumulated
spies within the Red Keep.

621
00:39:51.766 --> 00:39:53.976
Servants who knew the
comings and goings.

622
00:39:53.977 --> 00:39:55.936
Scheme with someone
else. Daemon.

623
00:39:55.937 --> 00:39:59.774
I was once in your
thrall. but no longer.

624
00:40:00.608 --> 00:40:02.485
A transaction. then.

625
00:40:03.028 --> 00:40:06.448
Your knowledge in
exchange for your freedom.

626
00:40:11.661 --> 00:40:14.039
(footsteps approaching)

627
00:40:19.002 --> 00:40:22.339
(light. solemn music playing)

628
00:40:33.683 --> 00:40:35.018
Your Grace.

629
00:40:36.227 --> 00:40:38.355
♪

630
00:40:38.480 --> 00:40:42.107
(emotional) Lady Jeyne Arryn
has pledged her support

631
00:40:42.108 --> 00:40:45.362
in exchange for a dragon
to guard the Vale.

632
00:40:47.906 --> 00:40:51.159
And Lord Cregan Stark...

633
00:40:53.870 --> 00:40:56.873
has promised 2.000 men...

634
00:41:02.253 --> 00:41:04.214
(both weeping)

635
00:41:04.339 --> 00:41:06.341
♪

636
00:41:12.555 --> 00:41:14.724
(door opens)

637
00:41:17.060 --> 00:41:19.062
♪

638
00:41:42.252 --> 00:41:43.920
Alyrie Florent.

639
00:41:44.421 --> 00:41:46.423
♪

640
00:42:02.731 --> 00:42:04.941
(music intensifies)

641
00:42:13.783 --> 00:42:15.952
Viserys Targaryen.

642
00:42:20.749 --> 00:42:22.959
♪

643
00:42:39.851 --> 00:42:42.103
♪

644
00:43:11.341 --> 00:43:15.512
(deep breath)
Lucerys Velaryon.

645
00:43:15.637 --> 00:43:17.639
♪

646
00:43:25.689 --> 00:43:27.857
(music fades out)

647
00:43:59.889 --> 00:44:01.849
(dog barking)

648
00:44:01.850 --> 00:44:04.602
(indistinct chatter)

649
00:44:04.728 --> 00:44:06.896
(Daemon whistles)

650
00:44:10.358 --> 00:44:11.443
A tribute.

651
00:44:11.568 --> 00:44:13.236
(coins jingle)

652
00:44:20.368 --> 00:44:21.786
Commander?

653
00:44:21.911 --> 00:44:24.080
Never gone for long.

654
00:44:25.540 --> 00:44:28.960
I'm told you bear a
mislike for the Hightowers.

655
00:44:30.086 --> 00:44:32.464
Fuck the Hightowers.

656
00:44:37.761 --> 00:44:39.428
Keep walking.

657
00:44:39.429 --> 00:44:41.473
(street chatter)

658
00:44:43.099 --> 00:44:45.268
Don't make trouble.

659
00:44:51.566 --> 00:44:52.941
(dog barks)

660
00:44:52.942 --> 00:44:54.401
Daemon Targaryen:
The White Worm said

661
00:44:54.402 --> 00:44:56.362
you're one of
Aegon's ratcatchers.

662
00:44:56.363 --> 00:45:00.408
You must be busy. That castle
positively crawls with them now.

663
00:45:01.451 --> 00:45:03.452
I heard the White
Worm were dead.

664
00:45:03.453 --> 00:45:05.788
Her ghost told me you
were a betting man.

665
00:45:05.789 --> 00:45:11.085
- Fighting pits?
- Dogs... and bones.

666
00:45:11.086 --> 00:45:13.129
How deep are your debts?

667
00:45:20.303 --> 00:45:22.138
I was also given to
understand that you possess

668
00:45:22.263 --> 00:45:24.431
a unique knowledge
of the Red Keep.

669
00:45:24.432 --> 00:45:26.309
Maegor's tunnels.

670
00:45:26.434 --> 00:45:28.520
Great big rat's nest. it is.

671
00:45:29.479 --> 00:45:32.774
I know them better than
the shape of my own cock.

672
00:45:35.151 --> 00:45:36.528
This is my friend.

673
00:45:37.654 --> 00:45:40.156
Tonight. he's going
to be your friend.

674
00:45:40.824 --> 00:45:44.160
You're to find and slay the
Prince Aemond Targaryen.

675
00:45:45.203 --> 00:45:47.830
He has silver hair and one eye.

676
00:45:47.831 --> 00:45:50.458
Should be easy enough to find.

677
00:45:52.002 --> 00:45:53.627
But I understand he's
quite good in a fight.

678
00:45:53.628 --> 00:45:55.547
You'll want to take caution.

679
00:45:57.048 --> 00:46:00.802
That's one half. You'll get
the other when it's done.

680
00:46:04.180 --> 00:46:06.349
(dog barking)

681
00:46:12.689 --> 00:46:14.024
Alright.

682
00:46:16.026 --> 00:46:17.819
What if we can't find him?

683
00:46:22.032 --> 00:46:25.826
We've wasted precious days in
this war of quills and ravens.

684
00:46:25.827 --> 00:46:28.705
Words are wind.

685
00:46:28.830 --> 00:46:31.040
You should be leading the van.

686
00:46:31.041 --> 00:46:33.500
and I should be flying
cover on Vhagar.

687
00:46:33.501 --> 00:46:36.879
No castle would dare to raise
Rhaenyra's banner against us.

688
00:46:36.880 --> 00:46:40.091
We would bring the whole of the
Crownlands to heel in weeks.

689
00:46:40.216 --> 00:46:43.010
Well. mayhaps we could
petition the king.

690
00:46:43.011 --> 00:46:46.264
privately. to send us out.

691
00:46:47.891 --> 00:46:49.641
Rosby and Stokeworth.

692
00:46:49.642 --> 00:46:53.145
small castles right in the
shadow of King's Landing.

693
00:46:53.146 --> 00:46:54.813
They would not want
us for enemies.

694
00:46:54.814 --> 00:46:57.233
We could add their
levies to our own.

695
00:46:58.234 --> 00:47:00.862
Our host growing as we advance.

696
00:47:03.031 --> 00:47:05.450
Uh. it is a canny scheme.

697
00:47:05.950 --> 00:47:07.410
But moot.

698
00:47:07.535 --> 00:47:10.455
My brother is hostage to
my grandsire and mother.

699
00:47:10.580 --> 00:47:14.084
and they tell him that a war
of dragons can yet be avoided.

700
00:47:14.209 --> 00:47:17.253
'Tis inevitable.
They must see that.

701
00:47:17.379 --> 00:47:19.714
Otto fears to upset
the order of things.

702
00:47:20.924 --> 00:47:23.093
And Alicent is simply...

703
00:47:24.052 --> 00:47:25.470
angry.

704
00:47:26.304 --> 00:47:29.682
- Angry?
- She blames me for starting this war

705
00:47:29.683 --> 00:47:34.145
after she plotted with my father's
council to usurp his throne.

706
00:47:35.563 --> 00:47:39.150
"Her Grace" speaks
with two tongues.

707
00:47:42.821 --> 00:47:45.073
She has a gentle heart.

708
00:47:45.573 --> 00:47:48.284
And Rhaenyra is
a cunning spider.

709
00:47:48.618 --> 00:47:52.788
Long ago. she drew
Alicent into her web...

710
00:47:52.789 --> 00:47:54.749
intoxicated her.

711
00:47:56.167 --> 00:47:58.294
It is not your mother's fault.

712
00:47:59.462 --> 00:48:01.840
She holds love for our enemy.

713
00:48:03.800 --> 00:48:05.802
That makes her a fool.

714
00:48:07.804 --> 00:48:09.638
(door opens)

715
00:48:09.639 --> 00:48:11.433
(footsteps approach)

716
00:48:22.485 --> 00:48:23.653
Lord Hand.

717
00:48:33.329 --> 00:48:35.247
Return to your post.
Lord Commander.

718
00:48:35.248 --> 00:48:37.667
I must have a word
with the prince.

719
00:48:49.721 --> 00:48:51.348
(door opens)

720
00:48:51.473 --> 00:48:53.183
It would concern me. grandson.

721
00:48:53.308 --> 00:48:54.684
if plans were being considered

722
00:48:54.809 --> 00:48:58.563
beyond the ears of
your king and his Hand.

723
00:48:59.147 --> 00:49:01.190
You have a zeal to
act. I understand.

724
00:49:01.191 --> 00:49:02.525
I was young once myself...

725
00:49:02.650 --> 00:49:05.862
I only wish to serve
my king and my house.

726
00:49:11.993 --> 00:49:13.411
You and Vhagar

727
00:49:13.536 --> 00:49:16.706
are the greatest single
power in the realm.

728
00:49:18.708 --> 00:49:22.504
If it wasn't obvious
before. it certainly is now.

729
00:49:27.217 --> 00:49:30.428
But there are many
pieces at play here...

730
00:49:31.388 --> 00:49:34.391
some of which you can't yet see.

731
00:49:35.100 --> 00:49:36.935
I promise you.
Aemond. you will have

732
00:49:37.060 --> 00:49:38.686
all the vengeance that you seek.

733
00:49:38.687 --> 00:49:42.524
but you must keep a
grip on your impulses.

734
00:49:45.068 --> 00:49:47.737
We both know that
your brother cannot.

735
00:49:50.907 --> 00:49:53.409
(street chatter)

736
00:49:53.410 --> 00:49:56.705
(tense music playing)

737
00:50:04.254 --> 00:50:06.631
- (dog whimpering)
- Cheese: Alright.

738
00:50:09.217 --> 00:50:11.428
♪

739
00:50:24.232 --> 00:50:26.443
♪

740
00:50:39.956 --> 00:50:41.332
Take that.

741
00:50:46.838 --> 00:50:48.590
Bring the dog.

742
00:50:49.257 --> 00:50:51.468
♪

743
00:51:13.031 --> 00:51:14.532
(laughter)

744
00:51:15.033 --> 00:51:17.493
Aegon: I need to be a
symbol for the smallfolk.

745
00:51:17.494 --> 00:51:19.371
- as well as the nobility.
- Cheese: Wait.

746
00:51:19.496 --> 00:51:21.163
Speaker: You could always be

747
00:51:21.164 --> 00:51:22.664
"Aegon the Strong."

748
00:51:22.665 --> 00:51:24.500
Aegon: My nephew's
already taken that one.

749
00:51:24.501 --> 00:51:26.335
- (laughter) - Leon: Well.
which would Your Grace prefer?

750
00:51:26.336 --> 00:51:28.213
- It's the king.
- Leon: To be loved or feared?

751
00:51:28.338 --> 00:51:29.588
Aegon: I need to be both.

752
00:51:29.589 --> 00:51:32.008
My mother and grandsire

753
00:51:32.133 --> 00:51:34.551
mind me like some
helpless duckling.

754
00:51:34.552 --> 00:51:36.388
Oh. well. you're the king.

755
00:51:36.513 --> 00:51:37.753
Who gives a shit what they say?

756
00:51:37.806 --> 00:51:40.516
My brother. at least.
knows his place.

757
00:51:40.517 --> 00:51:42.601
He's as loyal as a hound.

758
00:51:42.602 --> 00:51:46.356
I can set him and his
dragon on my foes at will.

759
00:51:47.857 --> 00:51:49.960
- Cheese: Keep your eyes down.
- Aegon: I need a style that

760
00:51:49.984 --> 00:51:53.363
demonstrates power
and commands respect.

761
00:51:53.488 --> 00:51:56.366
Eh. no-no one knows what
"magnanimous" means.

762
00:51:56.491 --> 00:51:58.992
- (group laughs) - Leon: You could
be "Aegon the Generous" then.

763
