the most rebellious.

1008
01:07:08.111 --> 01:07:09.611
<i>And Aegon often wins.</i>

1009
01:07:09.612 --> 01:07:10.612
He took my piece.

1010
01:07:10.780 --> 01:07:12.824
Is the heir to the throne
bothering you. Tyland?

1011
01:07:13.575 --> 01:07:15.493
We see him come into a
Small Council meeting

1012
01:07:15.618 --> 01:07:16.494
with Jaehaerys.

1013
01:07:16.619 --> 01:07:19.164
and. you know. he's
spurring him on.

1014
01:07:19.289 --> 01:07:22.750
He's wanting him to be more
of a... more of a rebel.

1015
01:07:22.751 --> 01:07:25.462
more of a nuisance.
just like his old man.

1016
01:07:25.587 --> 01:07:28.172
- I think he wants a ride.
- ALICENT HIGHTOWER: Your Grace.

1017
01:07:28.173 --> 01:07:30.008
- TYLAND LANNISTER: A ride?
- A pony ride.

1018
01:07:30.759 --> 01:07:32.134
Wouldn't that be fun. Jaehaerys?

1019
01:07:32.135 --> 01:07:34.512
Should the Master of
Coin be your royal steed?

1020
01:07:34.637 --> 01:07:35.971
(ALL CHUCKLING)

1021
01:07:35.972 --> 01:07:37.473
It's meant to be a
moment of fun. a bit.

1022
01:07:37.474 --> 01:07:40.642
And yes. like Aegon brings
his four-year-old to work.

1023
01:07:40.643 --> 01:07:42.811
<i>But I think on a perhaps
nuanced character level.</i>

1024
01:07:42.812 --> 01:07:45.439
this is the thing that
Viserys never did for Aegon.

1025
01:07:45.440 --> 01:07:47.316
And Aegon did not study
at the feet of his father.

1026
01:07:47.317 --> 01:07:49.777
His father had his male heir
and then essentially said.

1027
01:07:49.778 --> 01:07:52.030
"Well. that box is
ticked." He was ill.

1028
01:07:52.322 --> 01:07:53.655
<i>I think he enjoyed having a son.</i>

1029
01:07:53.656 --> 01:07:55.991
<i>but didn't put in the work
the way he did with Rhaenyra</i>

1030
01:07:55.992 --> 01:07:57.117
<i>when he was a younger man.</i>

1031
01:07:57.118 --> 01:07:58.828
And I think Aegon resents that

1032
01:07:59.037 --> 01:08:00.496
and feels that
part of the reason

1033
01:08:00.497 --> 01:08:02.164
that he's not seen
as being suited

1034
01:08:02.165 --> 01:08:04.334
for the crown or the throne

1035
01:08:04.501 --> 01:08:07.379
is because he didn't get that
training from his father.

1036
01:08:07.504 --> 01:08:10.048
so now he's going to
make up for that tenfold

1037
01:08:10.173 --> 01:08:11.341
<i>with Jaehaerys.</i>

1038
01:08:13.885 --> 01:08:16.053
ALAN: <i>Alicent's been in a
marriage that was loving.</i>

1039
01:08:16.054 --> 01:08:20.015
but not exactly romantic or
physical for quite some time.

1040
01:08:20.016 --> 01:08:21.850
Cole has got a lot of issues.

1041
01:08:21.851 --> 01:08:23.310
<i>One thing I love
about the character</i>

1042
01:08:23.311 --> 01:08:25.063
<i>is that he is a knight
in shining armor</i>

1043
01:08:25.188 --> 01:08:26.468
and sort of classically handsome

1044
01:08:26.523 --> 01:08:28.649
and probably the most messed
up person in the story

1045
01:08:28.650 --> 01:08:29.650
in many ways.

1046
01:08:29.818 --> 01:08:31.671
<i>You know. clinging to
notions of purity and duty</i>

1047
01:08:31.695 --> 01:08:34.322
<i>and just flagrantly breaking
them left and right.</i>

1048
01:08:34.698 --> 01:08:36.031
So. there's a lot
of complex things

1049
01:08:36.032 --> 01:08:37.866
driving the moves
closer and closer

1050
01:08:37.867 --> 01:08:39.077
between Alicent and Cole.

1051
01:08:39.369 --> 01:08:40.536
And it takes a leap forward.

1052
01:08:40.537 --> 01:08:41.817
<i>But nothing is simple with them.</i>

1053
01:08:41.871 --> 01:08:43.748
<i>so for every leap forward.
there's a push back.</i>

1054
01:08:44.082 --> 01:08:46.668
We cannot... again.

1055
01:08:46.918 --> 01:08:48.669
ALAN: <i>There's a lot of
wonderful tension there.</i>

1056
01:08:48.670 --> 01:08:51.839
I mean. I think there's love.
but there's a lot of mess too.

1057
01:08:51.840 --> 01:08:52.924
(LAUGHS)

1058
01:08:53.341 --> 01:08:54.842
- Your Grace.
- Good day.

1059
01:08:54.843 --> 01:08:56.344
FABIEN FRANKEL: <i>I
think. ultimately.</i>

1060
01:08:56.553 --> 01:09:01.725
they're two very lost people
in a pretty unforgiving world.

1061
01:09:02.058 --> 01:09:04.393
And I think there's always been.

1062
01:09:04.394 --> 01:09:06.438
<i>you know. since the
very first episode.</i>

1063
01:09:06.563 --> 01:09:08.355
<i>Alicent. you know. had
her eye on Criston Cole.</i>

1064
01:09:08.356 --> 01:09:10.357
<i>And then she was a young lady.</i>

1065
01:09:10.358 --> 01:09:13.737
<i>and now she's the Queen
of the Seven Kingdoms.</i>

1066
01:09:14.237 --> 01:09:16.739
OLIVIA COOKE: <i>It's paramount
that she keeps it a secret</i>

1067
01:09:16.740 --> 01:09:19.950
because not only
would her respect

1068
01:09:19.951 --> 01:09:22.077
completely disintegrate.

1069
01:09:22.078 --> 01:09:24.538
<i>but her stay in the castle.</i>

1070
01:09:24.539 --> 01:09:27.291
And Aegon is so unpredictable.
Who knows what he would do

1071
01:09:27.292 --> 01:09:31.128
if he found out that his
mother was having sex

1072
01:09:31.129 --> 01:09:33.298
with his Commander
of the Kingsguard?

1073
01:09:33.423 --> 01:09:35.215
I mean. not only is
it an embarrassment.

1074
01:09:35.216 --> 01:09:38.887
<i>it would bring deep. deep shame.</i>

1075
01:09:42.432 --> 01:09:45.101
I want Aemond Targaryen.

1076
01:09:46.478 --> 01:09:49.147
Rhaenyra has literally one
line in the first episode.

1077
01:09:49.272 --> 01:09:50.440
and the one line she says.

1078
01:09:50.774 --> 01:09:52.942
Daemon takes as
pulling the trigger.

1079
01:09:53.109 --> 01:09:55.779
In our first episode. we
see him unleash something

1080
01:09:55.904 --> 01:09:58.281
that is sort of famous in the
lore of <i>House of the Dragon.</i>

1081
01:09:58.448 --> 01:10:00.492
<i>a nasty event that he triggers.</i>

1082
01:10:00.950 --> 01:10:04.662
When Rhaenyra declares
that she wants Aemond.

1083
01:10:04.788 --> 01:10:09.668
<i>I think it's an admission of
a possibly shameful desire.</i>

1084
01:10:09.793 --> 01:10:12.796
<i>and I think that admission
is made directly to Daemon.</i>

1085
01:10:12.962 --> 01:10:15.964
I think it's also an
admission of their similarity.

1086
01:10:15.965 --> 01:10:18.968
<i>She sort of discloses
another way in which</i>

1087
01:10:19.094 --> 01:10:21.805
<i>they actually share a darkness.</i>

1088
01:10:22.472 --> 01:10:25.349
"I want Aemond Targaryen"
becomes the battle cry

1089
01:10:25.350 --> 01:10:27.643
that then resonates
across the entire season

1090
01:10:27.644 --> 01:10:30.312
because that is the
next domino to fall

1091
01:10:30.313 --> 01:10:32.940
<i>in this back and forth
that sets in motion</i>

1092
01:10:32.941 --> 01:10:34.859
<i>a horrible attack
and counterattack</i>

1093
01:10:34.984 --> 01:10:35.984
<i>that continues.</i>

1094
01:10:36.111 --> 01:10:38.488
<i>and the atrocities grow
worse and worse as they go.</i>

1095
01:10:38.988 --> 01:10:40.656
ALAN: <i>In our story.
it's Mysaria.</i>

1096
01:10:40.657 --> 01:10:42.825
who has got her tentacles into
every part of King's Landing.

1097
01:10:42.826 --> 01:10:44.993
who is able to provide
the connections

1098
01:10:44.994 --> 01:10:47.371
for Daemon to exact revenge.

1099
01:10:47.372 --> 01:10:48.997
<i>I think it really is a
big deal for the fans</i>

1100
01:10:48.998 --> 01:10:50.438
<i>because it keeps
getting referred to.</i>

1101
01:10:50.500 --> 01:10:52.459
And I don't know the
characters' actual names.

1102
01:10:52.460 --> 01:10:54.712
They're forever in lore
as Blood and Cheese.

1103
01:10:54.713 --> 01:10:57.131
- (LAUGHING)
- Who the fuck is she?

1104
01:10:57.132 --> 01:10:58.674
She's the Queen. she is.

1105
01:10:58.675 --> 01:11:00.634
"A son for a son." he said.

1106
01:11:00.635 --> 01:11:02.177
The boldest thing that
I think we did there

1107
01:11:02.178 --> 01:11:04.889
was decide to give the last
ten minutes of the episode

1108
01:11:05.015 --> 01:11:07.517
over to these two characters
that we have never met before

1109
01:11:07.642 --> 01:11:10.394
<i>and rely on them to take us
through the end of the story</i>

1110
01:11:10.395 --> 01:11:12.021
and to see. hopefully.

1111
01:11:12.022 --> 01:11:14.023
as they go deeper and
deeper into the Red Keep

1112
01:11:14.024 --> 01:11:16.002
and as we're spending more
and more screen time on them

1113
01:11:16.026 --> 01:11:18.403
that something horrible is
going to happen in there.

1114
01:11:18.528 --> 01:11:20.863
and knowing that you're
watching <i>Game of Thrones</i>

1115
01:11:20.864 --> 01:11:23.700
and you don't know what is going
to come for you from where.

1116
01:11:23.908 --> 01:11:25.826
<i>And seeing that play
out hopefully is the fun</i>

1117
01:11:25.827 --> 01:11:28.747
and the horror for the
audience that's yet to come.

1118
01:11:29.039 --> 01:11:31.249
♪ (MUSIC SWELLS) ♪

1119
01:11:31.374 --> 01:11:32.584
(MUFFLED YELP)

1120
01:11:33.585 --> 01:11:35.170
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES)
